ANOTHER KZN taxi boss is facing the law for being in possession of unlicensed firearms.The taxi owner appeared in the Nongoma Magistrates Court on Wednesday after being found with a revolver, pistol and bullets. His case was remanded to 29 November for further investigation. Lieutenant-Colonel Thulani Zwane said the recovered firearms will be sent for ballistic tests to establish if they were used in any taxi-related incidents in the province.&ldquo;Last Wednesday night police conducted an operation in the Nongoma area after receiving a tip-off. &ldquo;The cops went to a homestead, where they met the taxi owner,&rdquo; said Zwane.The suspect was found in possession of .38 revolver and a 9mm pistol with ammunition. &ldquo;He could not produce any licences to possess these firearms. He was then arrested and charged,&rdquo; said Zwane. Last Tuesday another taxi boss was bust for being in possession of illegal firearms, including two R5 rifles and an AK-47 in Verulam, north of Durban.Major-General Bheki Langa, the acting KZN police commissioner, encouraged residents to continue giving information to the police about people who are in possession of illegal firearms. &ldquo;These firearms are often used to commit serious violent crimes in the province and we must get rid of them. &ldquo;The police will continue with their operations in confiscating firearms.&ldquo;Criminals will face the long arm of the law,&rdquo; he said.